<p><strong></strong><strong>Instructions for New </strong><strong>Online Adjunct Faculty</strong><br /><br />1. Print, complete, and return BYU-Idaho employment paperwork as follows (please use a black pen and print clearly)<br /><br /><a href="Documents/human-resources/Online Adjunct PAR form.pdf">Personnel Action Request (PAR Form)</a> <br /><a href="Documents/human-resources/ConditionsofEmploymentForm.pdf">Acknowledgement of Conditions of Employment</a> <br /><a href="http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/fw4.pdf" target="_self">Federal Withholding Form W-4</a> <br /><a href="x34755.xml">State Withholding Form</a> (form varies based on state of residence)<br /><a href="Documents/human-resources/DirectDepositForm.pdf">Direct Deposit Form</a> (please include a voided check) <br /><a href="Documents/human-resources/EmpInfoUsageAgreement.pdf">Employee Information Usage Agreement</a> <br /><a href="Documents/human-resources/WorkRelatedInjuriesForm.pdf">Work-Related Injuries and Illnesses</a> <br /><a href="x34756.xml">Form I-9</a>&nbsp;<br /><br />Please send completed paperwork to:<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heather Hall, Hiring Coordinator<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BYU-Idaho Online Learning<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 525 South Center, Mail Stop 4620<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rexburg, ID 83460-4620<br /><br />2. After your employment paperwork has been received and processed, you will receive email correspondence from BYU-Idaho's Human Resources Office with instructions to set up your BYU-Idaho username and password. This process will also assign you an email address.<br /><br />3. You will also be sent an email with instructions regarding the BYU-Idaho Privacy Tutorial, which you are required to take before access can be granted to confidential information.<br /><br /></p>
